item.title: 9/11 alleged mastermind Khalid Sheikh Mohammed and 2 others reach plea deal
item.description: Three of the five 9/11 defendants at Guantanamo have reached a plea agreement with prosecutors, the Department of Defense announced Wednesday.

item.description: Airlines would be required to put kids 13 and under next to an accompanying adult for free under a new proposed rule.

item.description: Police in India tell CBS News an American woman was found chained to a tree in a jungle, and she told them her husband left her to "die there."

item.title: Man 'intentionally' runs over flock of 25 seagulls with his jeep at the beach: Police
item.description: A man has “intentionally” run over and killed a flock of 25 seagulls with his Jeep Cherokee before almost running over two people and their dogs, authorities said.

item.description: Israel's military says it killed Hamas military commander Mohammed Deif in Gaza weeks before the assassinations of 2 other leaders of Hamas and Hezbollah.
